<div><h3>SPAN 245 - Latin American Short Genres </h3>  <hr>Introduces the tradition and development of short narrative in Hispanic America, from its beginnings in colonial chroniclers through the progressive refinements of theme, local color, style and narrative technique that led to fictions of the 20th-century &#8220;boom&#8221; and beyond. Conducted in Spanish.<br><br><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> <a href="preview_course_nopop.php?catoid=28&coid=94214" onclick="acalogPopup('preview_course.php?catoid=28&coid=94214&print', '3', 770, 530, 'yes');return false;" rel="remote /ajax/preview_course.php?catoid=28&coid=94214&display_options[location]=tooltip&show" id="tt8883" target="_blank">SPAN 131</a><span style="display: none !important">&#160;</span>, or <a href="preview_course_nopop.php?catoid=28&coid=95541" onclick="acalogPopup('preview_course.php?catoid=28&coid=95541&print', '3', 770, 530, 'yes');return false;" rel="remote /ajax/preview_course.php?catoid=28&coid=95541&display_options[location]=tooltip&show" id="tt2270" target="_blank">SPAN 132</a><span style="display: none !important">&#160;</span>, or by permission.<br><br><strong>Course Designation/Attribute:</strong> LP & DI<br><br><strong>Anticipated Terms Offered:</strong> Offered periodically<br><br><strong>Placement Guidelines</strong><br> Please visit the <a href="http://www.clarku.edu/departments/foreign/undergraduate/placement.cfm" target="_blank">Department of Language, Literature and Culture</a> for the language placement guidelines.<br><br><div style="display: none; z-index: 1000;" class="tooltip for_tt8883"></div><div style="display: none; z-index: 1000;" class="tooltip for_tt2270"></div></div>		</td>
